I think the code would be a lot simpler if we used a ScheduledExecutorService instead of this Timer.
Here's what I'm thinking:

We declare two fields:
    private final ScheduledExecutorService _scheduledExecutorService;
    private Future<?> _zkSessionExpiryFuture = CompletableFuture.completedFuture(null);

We change cancelTimer() to do:
_zkSessionExpiryFuture.cancel(false);

We change scheduleExpiryTimerAfterSessionTimeout() to do:
 _zkSessionExpiryFuture =
      _scheduledExecutorService.schedule(ZkAdapter.this::onSessionExpired, _sessionTimeoutMs,
          TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);

